#compdef portspoof
# Documentation: source-direct extraction from upstream
# drk1wi/portspoof src/Configuration.cpp `Configuration::usage`
# function body + the getopt argstring `"l:i:p:s:c:f:n:t:T:dvh12D"`
# in `Configuration::parse_arguments` (decoded by reading the
# case 'X': arms in main()).
# Reference accessed: 2026-05-30 via gh api.
# drk1wi Portspoof R158b — port-scanner deception tool: returns
# valid service banners for ALL closed TCP ports so a port scanner
# (nmap, masscan etc.) sees 65535 open ports with random services
# instead of the real ones. Used as a defensive measure on bastion
# hosts. Sister tool to the offensive-side family in the corpus
# (nmap/masscan/zmap/rustscan/subjack/subfinder).

_arguments -s -S \
  '-i+[bind to particular IP address]:ip:_hosts' \
  '-p+[bind to particular TCP port]:port:' \
  '-s+[Portspoof service signature regex file]:file:_files' \
  '-c+[Portspoof configuration file]:file:_files' \
  '-l+[log port-scanning alerts to a file]:file:_files' \
  '-f+[FUZZER_MODE: fuzzing payload file list]:file:_files' \
  '-n+[FUZZER_MODE: wrapping signatures file list]:file:_files' \
  '(-2)-1[FUZZER_MODE: generate fuzzing payloads internally]' \
  '(-1)-2[switch to simple reply mode (does NOT work for Nmap detection)]' \
  '-t+[minimum hold time in seconds (default 0)]:sec:' \
  '-T+[maximum hold time in seconds (default 120)]:sec:' \
  '-D[run as daemon process]' \
  '-d[disable syslog]' \
  '-v[verbose output]' \
  '-h[display help and exit]'
